		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thanks for the answer.  I will check with a meter tonight to see if all of them are wired or not. 
<br />
<br />At first I was worried when I saw the image of the board I want to use on the bootgod database (<a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/profile.php?id=2236" class="postlink">here</a>) since the last pins (from the front of the board) seems to all be connected to the same place. But after searching more, 256k game had the same board so it should not be an issue. It just seems that TLROM JP board and US board are a little bit different in design.

		

