	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><img src="http://img513.imageshack.us/img513/8980/boardgx8.jpg" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />Assuming that the CHIP is a standard nintendo one (and I don't see why it wouldn't be, even though the cart is japanese), you just have to worry about the holes I circled in red.
<br />
<br />We can clearly see that the bottom ones are VCC, because they are connected to the hole at their left, so these are correct. The top 2 should be connected to A18 and A17 on the MMC3. Check the the pinout of the MMC3 <a href="http://www.tripoint.org/kevtris/mappers/mmc3/index.html" class="postlink">here</a> so that you know which pins are those on the MMC3.
<br />
<br />There is some confusion regarding A17 and A18 of the MMC3 because the <a href="http://nesdev.com/rom.txt" class="postlink">document at the NESDEV page</a> seems to have them mixed up. I'm almost certain that this document is wrong, while the one at Kevin horton's page (linked above) is correct.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


